<chapter xml:id="ch-background" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Important Background Mathematics</title>

  <introduction>
    <p>
      As we will see throughout this course, nearly all of the analysis will be based on theorems from Calculus.
      In this chapter, we will review the important theorems and concepts from Calculus.
    </p>
    <p>
      This will be a brief reminder of these topics.  Note that typically these are covered in detailed over three courses: Precalculus, Differential Calculus and Series.  Much of this can be found in more detail in texts like <url href="https://www.apexcalculus.com">APEX Calculus</url>.
    </p>
  </introduction>

